==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[common|Common]] [[era|Era]]'''  (abbreviated as ''[[CE]]'')

# The Christian Era.
#* '''1913''': ''The Catholic Encyclopedia'' - Foremost among these (dating eras) is that which is now adopted by all civilized peoples and known as the Christian, Vulgar or '''Common Era''', in the twentieth century of which we are now living.
#* '''2005''': ''Maryland Church News Submission Guide & Style Manual'' - Instead of AD and BC, use BCE and CE (Before Common Era and '''Common Era''').
#* '''2006''': The Smithsonian Institution, ''World History Standards'' - Expanding Zones of Exchange and Encounter, 300-1000 '''CE'''

====Usage notes====
Used primarily by Jewish writers and some US academics as an alternative to anno Domini or AD.

